or) on a raid isn't a rare thing.  So in the high end raid area of things, warriors still have a solid place and still do some very good DPS.<br>
<br>
<br>
The other area to talk about is 45-59ish small raid guilds and exp groups.  One major factor here is that taunt is still mostly 'broken' as designed from 50-59.  For all intents and purposes during those levels you really aren't a warrior.  There's things you can do if you try hard to kind of fake it.  But in reality you really aren't a real warrior until you hit level 60.  Then everything changes.  During this time and 2 hell levels there's a lot of frustration.  And guilds in this range find a lot of problems with controlling aggro and often find it best to have paladins and SK tank most mobs.  This is still even a problem for smaller guilds and exp groups for 60 warriors who don't have good taunt weapons.  It IS really the case that we are more reliant on the weapon in our hands than any other class.  Many warriors struggle or quit in this situation.  But once a warrior finally gets 60 and finally tracks down his epic, willsapper, Ichorflow, etc, they can finally appreciate being a warrior.  And at this point if you've still got pal/sks stealing aggro from you and tanking.  It's not a problem with you, it's a problem with them.<br>
<br>
It is a valid argument that hybrids, rogues, monks can do much better in exp groups than warriors.  But at the same time it all depends on what zone you are in and what classes are in the group.  With these new free exp zones (which IMFO ruin a lot of the game) like Velks, FG, etc.  A warrior can make one hell of a group.  Specially a troll with a fungi vest.  You just have to know what to do and how to do it.  Grab yourself a few of those detested hybrids and rogue/monks and goto town.  You can rake in exp with massive DPS and with your tanking skill and regen it only takes a ranger/paladin to heal you (if you need heals at all).  If anyone should be mad here, it should be clerics and druids.  Because in these 'free exp' zones shaman are great in groups and can keep up a solid DPS, plus buffs, and regen.  No melee group in their right minds would refuse a shaman.  But not many melee groups in these situations would want a druid or cleric.  Unless you think that Judgement has great DPS... druid's damage shield is helpful a bit, but you can just get that from click items or a ranger.<br>
<br>
In general, if you aren't happy with the warrior class then do these things:<br>
<br>
1) Get level 60. Don't @#%$ bitch about it either, it is SO EASY TO DO NOW!<br>
2) Get good aggro weapons.  Yes, you might have to @#%$ camp Sev, Vaniki, Grieg, etc.<br>
<br>
If you've done that and you still can't hold aggro or your guild won't let you tank then, join another guild.<br>
<br>
If you are in a guild and you actively tank stuff, and you are level 60 and have good aggro weapons and STILL think that warriors are screwed....<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  THEN QUIT AND GO PLAY ANOTHER CLASS. </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<br>
You'll likely come back when you notice the grass wasn't really greener. <p><a href="http://www.akanon.org/view_profile.php?num=12">Gurgel Troll Warlord</a><br>
