<br>
Gurgel is right, exp in luclin is so stupidly easy that the only requirement for an exp group is DPS, and the more the better.  If I put a cleric in my group in FG/ME/Akheva, it's because I'm doin em a favor, and they damn well better have all of their nukes loaded hehe.  <br>
<br>
Warriors are, and will remain, the best tanks in the game.  They are, and always have been, one of the least versatile classes in the game.  Get used to it if you want to play a warrior.  <br>
<br>
Incidentally, I'm having almost the exact same discussion over on the casters realm warrior board hehe.  The question I asked over there is, what did hybrids get that made them suddenly so overpowered in relation to warriors?  They got a DPS upgrade with better weapons and improvements to 2-handers (which also benefits warriors).  They got undead crits (nice, but very situational), and um...a free horse?  help me out here.  This stuff makes them a better tank than you, when they used to be nothing but a HT taker?  Hybrids have *always* been able to tank in exp groups.  Do you think that they shouldn't?  They have always been able to heal/stun/root and get more aggro than a warrior.<br>
<br>
How exactly did Verant &quot;go overboard&quot; improving hybrids and make them so much better than warriors?  The only thing I see was that they got a dps upgrade, with the intention of making them do 85% of the damage that warriors do. I suspect they do more than that with some uber 2-handers, but in general, sub-level 60 paladins do significantly less dps than warriors.<br>
<br>
