<br>
However, our selection of class abilities is very poor in comparison to some of the others. Yes, Summon Horse is not game breaking, but damn that is a nice one to have isn't it.<br>
<br>
What about you? After Area Taunt, what class abilities are really that good?<br>
<br>
Slay Undead makes a paladin unstoppable in the situations where undead mobs are pulled. Have you ever seen one in KC basement? My god. What do we have? Rampage? Ok maybe if we acquire an Earthshaker, that skill is pretty damn cool. It doesn't turn us into the soloing juggurnaut that the Slay Undead Paladin is.<br>
<br>
Flurry is extremely poor benefit vs. cost. Hopefully we get a few cool abilities with PoP out. I don't mean anything like Slay Undead... just... something better than War Cry!<br>
<br>
&quot;Increased Taunt&quot; (like the enchanter hate increaser, but not as powerful) or &quot;Crippling Kick&quot; (always critical on kicks) innate abilities for points of class AA would be something that I would very much look forward to. The taunt skill may be over the line, but one can hope.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I'm pleased that the Knights finally are in line with our overall gaming experience. I don't think the fundamentals of the warrior class needs to be changed. However, I strongly agree with the argument that we are shortchanged when it comes to the 60+ aa mark. <p><table border="0">
