<br>
Well, it wasnt' almost overnight, it was a series of upgrades that started last year.   First was a manapool increase, which all agreed was a good thing.  Then was the increase in defense skill to the exact same as warriors.   Previously, there wasn't any question that pallys COULD outtaunt wariors, they just didnt' want to cause they'd get their asses whupped.   Then was the advent of the vastly superior weapons throught mid velious, along with that came the damage table increases which put them on the same damage tables as warriors (who were on a different, higher table), then came AA points, and All Melee armors, which have been historically class specific.   Any of these things by themselves isn't that big of a deal, but add them all up, and the difference intanking power of Paladins and SK's from before to now is INSANE.   Now, they've always had, as I said earlier the ability to outtaunt warriors, it was just stupid to do so.  Now it's different, warriors have nothing over them aside from being able to tank the big boys.  This is even true in melee combat, where warriors should, at least in MY vision, have a decided advantage both offensively AND defensively to compensate for not having the advantage of utility.<br>
