<br>
Both Slay Undead 1,2,3 and Flurry 1,2,3 require 3 levels of Combat Fury.<br>
<br>
The difference is that SU is actually tremendously powerful against undead in practice. Flurry... is not as exciting.<br>
<br>
It's not the end-all, be-all of the AA world. But it *is* a data point. Look at monks with rapid feign and improved mend... our &quot;expensive badass skill&quot; which apparently is supposed to be Flurry given the pre-reqs and the class AA cost is just underwhelming in comparison. <p><table border="0">
